<p><strong>GRAIN - Global Relations in Academia and INdustry</strong></p>
<p><br>
<strong>Vision</strong><br>
To bridge the gap between industry and academia, with students as the main =
resources</p>
<p><br>
<strong>Mission</strong><br>
</p>
<ul>
<li>Knowledge capture of prior work&#8212;IC &amp; SR, Placement, Shaastra,=
 RSD</li><li>Knowledge generation via survey of industry &amp; academia</li=
><li>Perform gap analysis</li><li>Where are industry expectations not being=
 met?</li><li>Where are academic expectations not being met?</li><li>Assess=
 how students can help bridge the gap</li></ul>
<p><br>
<strong>Schedule</strong><br>
</p>
<ul>
<li>Initial: (by Dec 31)</li><li>Form small student team</li><li>Knowledge =
capture of prior work -- IC &amp; SR, Placement, Shaastra, RSD</li><li>Form=
ulate surveys&#8212;industry, academia, students</li><li>Conduct surveys</l=
i><li>Perform gap analysis</li><li>Plan for long-term activities</li><li>Lo=
ng-Term: (after Jan 1, 2017)</li><li>Expand student team as needed.</li><li=
>Based on initial work done, update the long term tasks.</li><li>Ongoing: v=
isits to and from industry</li><li>Weekly: Alternating each week - industry=
 lectures on campus, academic lectures in industry.</li><li>Monthly: Strate=
gic review of ongoing progress and gain inputs</li><li>Once a semester: Col=
lective workshops to build consensus</li></ul>
<p><br>
<strong>Planned Approach/ Steps</strong><br>
</p>
<ul>
<li>Build small team for performing initial tasks</li><li>Knowledge capture=
 of prior work</li><li>Formulate, and conduct surveys - iterate as needed</=
li><li>Comprehensive analysis of gaps</li><li>Ideate and discuss activities=
 with industry members</li><li>Hold weekly talks in industry and academia</=
li><li>Hold first workshop/summit around 2nd week of January</li><li>Collab=
orate with various student teams in the institute for formulating and execu=
ting a strategy.</li><li>Strategic review of ongoing progress and gain inpu=
ts: Periodic (monthly)</li></ul>
